文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: Uniaxial tension creep tests have been conducted on polycrystalline alpha zirconium from 50 to 850 C

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: From 50 to 300 C the activation energy for creep was stress-dependent increasing from approximately 30 to 75 kcal/mole when the stress was decreased from 800 to 400 kg/cm²

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: Between 300 and 400 C, the activation energy is approximately 70 kcal/mole

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: From 400 to 500 C, the activation energy increased from 70 to 105 kcal/mole with decreasing stress

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: From 500 to 700 C, the activation energy was lower with an average value of 66 kcal/mole

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: From 700 to 800 C, the activation energy was 100 kcal/mole independent of stress

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: The apparent activation energy decreased to a very low value above 800 C

文献ID: STP458-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_1st Volume_016_chunk1
证据片段: The creep behavior of alpha zirconium was somewhat different, depending upon whether the specimen was obtained from material fabricated and heat treated in the alpha phase or the beta phase

证据片段: Tests were conducted in static helium purified at BNWL to less than 1 ppm combined moisture and oxygen
